            </tr>

        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>
</p>
<p>Symfony never renders this <em>whole</em> template at once, just each block, as it needs them.
It's almost like a list of small functions, where each function, or block, renders
just a small part of the form.</p>
<h2 id="the-bootstramp-theme">The Bootstramp Theme <a class="headerlink" href="pro-form-theming#the-bootstramp-theme" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>But in reality, not all of <em>our</em> markup is coming from this one file. In an
<a href="../symfony-forms/render-form-bootstrap">earlier tutorial</a>, we started using the Bootstrap form <em>theme</em>.
Open <code>app/config/config.yml</code> and find the <code>twig.form_themes</code> key:</p>
