<p>What about rendering the <em>label</em> for a <em>textarea</em>? We'd expect this to be <code>textarea_label</code>.
Find that. Ooh, it's not here! This is because the field types follow a <em>hierarchy</em>.
First, Symfony looks for <code>textarea_label</code>. But if that's not there, it'll fallback
to its parent type: text. So, <code>text_label</code>. And if <em>that</em> doesn't exist, it'll finally
look for - and find - <code>form_label</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="3c05fde198">
